Java `` - Create a new project. mkdocs serve - Start the live-reloading docs server. mkdocs build - Build the documentation site. mkdocs -h - Print help message and exit. Git Sort branches by commits: Here is a simple command that lists all branches with latest commits: git branch -v To order by most recent commit, use git branch -v --sort=committerdate git for-each-ref --sort=-committerdate refs/heads/ Or using git branch (since version 2.7.0) git branch --sort=-committerdate # DESC git branch --sort=committerdate # ASC
